wikipedia_page.main: James Walter McFarlane (12 December 1920, Sunderland – 9 August 1999, Stody, Norfolk) was a scholar of European literature, author of The Oxford Ibsen, and founding Dean of the School of European Studies at University of East Anglia which included Scandinavian studies.

response: *The Oxford Ibsen, edited by James McFarlane (Oxford, 1960-1977). The most comprehensive version available.

In 1841 an early settler, James McFarlane, described the district as resembling "a field of waving corn", and called it "Hayfield".  By 1866, the spelling had changed to "Heyfield", but exactly when and why this happened is unclear., , ,  It may have been renamed to reflect the spelling of the nearby Heyfield Station.Heyfield, Victoria - Travelmate
